%U A398145 1140812140619151000,62991219747882801375,3717493171921698419250,233519782906293185176875,15556451508813488057284500
%N A398145 Number of rooted binary simplex time-consistent leaf-labeled galled trees with n leaves.
%H A398145 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A398145/b398145.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..369</a>
%H A398145 Lily Agranat-Tamir, Michael Fuchs, Bernhard Gittenberger, Noah A. Rosenberg, Karthik V. Seetharaman, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aam.2026.103131">Combinatorial comparison of general galled trees, time-consistent galled trees, and simplex time-consistent galled trees</a>, Adv. Appl. Math. 180, 103131 (2026). See Table 4.
%F A398145 E.g.f. satisfies A(x) = x + (1/2)*A(x)^2 + (x/2)*(A(x)/(1-A(x)))^2.
%e A398145 For n=3 leaves, there are 3 rooted binary leaf-labeled trees with three leaves and no galls: ((A,B),C), ((A,C),B), and ((B,C),A). There are 3 rooted binary simplex time-consistent leaf-labeled galled trees with a root gall from which three leaves are descended, one each for the three distinct labels for the single leaf that descends from the reticulation node. Hence, a(3)=3+3=6.
%Y A398145 Cf. A001147 (rooted binary leaf-labeled trees with n leaves and 0 galls), A328122 (rooted binary leaf-labeled general galled trees with n leaves), A394516 (rooted binary time-consistent leaf-labeled galled trees with n leaves).
